---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="ArcOS — Windows Configuration Framework"
    description="ArcOS is a modular Windows configuration framework that applies a reproducible, performance-focused system profile without modifying or redistributing Windows."
    keywords="ArcOS, Windows configuration framework, Windows optimization, Windows deployment, PowerShell framework"
    activePage="projects"
    ogType="article"
>
    <!-- PAGE HERO -->
    <section class="page-hero">
        <div class="hero-glow glow-1"></div>
        <div class="hero-glow glow-2"></div>

        <div class="page-hero-content fade-up" style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 3rem; text-align: left; max-width: 1100px; width: 100%;">
            
            <!-- Left -->
            <div style="flex: 0 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem;">
                <img src="/arctext.png" alt="ArcOS" style="width: 200px; height: auto; display: block;"/>
                <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1.1rem; opacity: 0.7;">
                    Deterministic Windows configuration. No custom ISO.
                </p>
                <a href="/assets/WallpaperKit.zip" class="btn-primary" style="align-self: flex-start;">
                    Wallpaper Kit
                </a>
            </div>

            <!-- Right -->
            <div class="arc-preview" style="flex: 1 1 0; min-width: 0; border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); box-shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);">
                <img src="/wallpaper.png" alt="ArcOS Preview" style="width: 100%; height: auto; display: block;"/>
            </div>

        </div>

    </section>

    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <section class="content-block">
        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="content-grid">
                <div class="fade-up">
                    <div class="section-number">00</div>
                    <h2 class="section-title">What ArcOS Actually Is</h2>

                    <p class="section-desc">
                        ArcOS is a Windows configuration framework — not a custom operating system.
                        It applies a structured, reproducible set of configuration rules to a clean
                        Windows installation.
                    </p>

                    <p class="section-desc" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
                        The project focuses on reducing unnecessary background services,
                        removing consumer-facing features, and applying supported system
                        policies in a controlled and reversible way.
                    </p>

                    <p class="section-desc" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
                        ArcOS does not redistribute Windows, modify system binaries,
                        or patch the kernel. It operates within supported configuration
                        boundaries.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="fade-up">
                    <div class="project-detail-card">
                        <div
                            class="project-detail-header"
                            style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #020d1f, #0f2a5c);"
                        >
                            <span
                                class="project-tag"
                                style="color: #2563eb; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.1);"
                            >Windows Framework</span>
                            <h3 style="color: #fff;">ArcOS</h3>
                        </div>

                        <div class="project-detail-body">
                            <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                                Modular, deterministic, reversible.
                            </p>

                            <ul class="project-features">
                                <li>Manifest-driven engine execution</li>
                                <li>Risk-tiered configuration profiles</li>
                                <li>Windows build compatibility validation</li>
                                <li>Rollback state tracking</li>
                                <li>Deployment reporting</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ARCHITECTURE -->
    <section class="content-block alt">
        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="section-number fade-up">01</div>
            <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Architecture</h2>

            <p class="section-desc fade-up" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                ArcOS is built as a modular execution framework composed of isolated engines.
            </p>

            <div class="values-grid">

                <div class="value-card fade-up">
                    <h3>Modular Engines</h3>
                    <p>
                        Services, scheduled tasks, AppX packages, policies,
                        performance tuning, and UI configuration are handled
                        by independent engines.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="value-card fade-up">
                    <h3>Manifest-Driven Execution</h3>
                    <p>
                        Engine metadata defines risk level, compatibility,
                        and reboot requirements. Playbooks determine execution order.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="value-card fade-up">
                    <h3>Deterministic</h3>
                    <p>
                        Configuration is idempotent and reproducible.
                        Re-running ArcOS results in the same validated state.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="value-card fade-up">
                    <h3>Reversible</h3>
                    <p>
                        Restore points and state tracking are created prior
                        to modification, enabling controlled rollback.
                    </p>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BOUNDARIES -->
    <section class="content-block">
        <div class="content-container fade-up" style="text-align: center;">
            <div class="section-number">02</div>
            <h2 class="section-title">What ArcOS Does Not Do</h2>

            <ul class="project-features" style="margin-top: 2rem; display: inline-block; text-align: left;">
                <li>No custom Windows ISO</li>
                <li>No kernel patching</li>
                <li>No binary modification</li>
                <li>No Windows component redistribution</li>
                <li>No update servicing stack interference</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="content-block" style="text-align: center; padding-bottom: 6rem;">
        <div class="content-container fade-up">
            <h2 class="section-title">Open Source & Transparent</h2>
            <p class="section-desc" style="margin: 0 auto 2rem;">
                ArcOS is open source and available under the GNU GPL-3.0 license.
                Review the engines, modify playbooks, or build your own profiles.
            </p>

            <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
                <a
                    href="https://github.com/criminas/arcos"
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noopener"
                    class="btn-primary">View Source</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Structured Data -->
    <script
        type="application/ld+json"
        set:html={JSON.stringify({
            "@context": "https://schema.org",
            "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
            name: "ArcOS",
            applicationCategory: "UtilitiesApplication",
            operatingSystem: "Windows",
            offers: {
                "@type": "Offer",
                price: "0",
                priceCurrency: "USD"
            },
            description:
                "ArcOS is a modular Windows configuration framework that applies a reproducible system profile without modifying or redistributing Windows.",
            featureList: [
                "Manifest-driven execution",
                "Risk-tiered configuration",
                "Windows build validation",
                "Rollback tracking",
                "Deployment reporting"
            ],
            author: {
                "@type": "Organization",
                name: "Criminas"
            }
        })}
    />
</Layout>